name: Bali Outbound & Farmstay (BOF)
address: Banjar Baturiti Kaja, Kec. Baturiti, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82161, Indonesia
review 1: pretty good place for simple camping or group events. toilets are cones but rudimentary. showers func  fyi on with hot water but very basic. can pick/eat beans, carrots and chilis which were excellent. food provided was basic indonesia food but fine. they set up tents before arrival and staff was thoughtful and professional. no luxury here but passable.
review 2: i suggest you to choose  this place to your outbound activity . because it can accommodate around 500 people. with a cool atmosphere, green grass and beautiful hill views. there are several facilities in this place such as swings, fish ponds, gazebos, and of course the toilets are quite a lot scattered in every corner of the field. the entry ticket is also very cheap, only  IDR 2OK/ person. access to this place is also good because previous we come with 14 buses and it was still safe.
review 3: Huge outdoor activities area with hot water bathrooms.  Friendly host as well.   I've been here a few times now and so far it's been great.  Camping for a couple nights with great views of nearby mountains and to the south city lights in the distance.  Great place to bring the kids who can play to their heart's content all day long.  The owners also provide a fire pit and wood. A 10 min drive away is the main road to Bedugul where you will find restaurants and mini marts.  Walking distance from the camp is a huge forest offering great walks.
review 4: Really well organised camping ground with all the needed facilities.
review 5: Awesome camping experience! Great mountain view and fresh air

name: KEBUN NANG ANDRE
address: M5GJ+H5M, Angseri, Baturiti, Tabanan Regency, Bali, Indonesia
